Germany is home to approximately 12,000 castles (either still standing or in ruins), with that number going up to 20,000 if the castles in what was once the Holy Roman Empire (which includes parts of present day Austria, Italy, and Switzerland) are also included.;
By the time a person reaches age 21 they will have pooped 6,552 pounds (2,972 kilograms). This amount will increase to 25,896 pounds (11,746 kilograms) by the age of 83.;
Honey never spoils. Archaeologists have discovered pots of honey in ancient Egyptian tombs that are over 3,000 years old and still perfectly edible.;
The shortest war in history took place between Britain and Zanzibar in 1896. It lasted only 38 minutes!;
The largest snowflake ever recorded was 15 inches wide and 8 inches thick. It fell in Fort Keogh, Montana, in 1887.;
The shortest scheduled commercial flight in the world is between the islands of Westray and Papa Westray in Scotland. The flight lasts just 47 seconds!;
The Hawaiian alphabet has only 12 letters.;
